SIMPLE: mongrel
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mongrel
<hw>Mon"grel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. shortened fr.
<ets>mongrel</ets>, and akin to AS. <ets>mengan</ets> to mix, and E.
<ets>mingle</ets>. See <er>Mingle</er>.]</ety> <def>The progeny
resulting from a cross between two breeds, as of domestic animals;
anything of mixed breed.</def> <rj><au>Drayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mongrel</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mongrel
<hw>Mon"grel</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Not
of a pure breed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Of mixed kinds; <as>as, <ex>mongrel</ex>
language</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mongrelize</ent>⟦br⟧
